SIMPLE: waking
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waking
<hw>Wak"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of waking, or
the state or period of being awake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A watch; a watching.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧Bodily pain . . . standeth in prayer, in <xex>wakings</xex>, in
fastings.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the fourth <qex>waking</qex> of the night.</q> <rj><qau>Wyclif
(Matt. xiv. 25).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Walaway</ent>⟦br⟧
